    <div class="text-container">
      <div class="text">
        <h3>Problem</h3>
        <p>After addressing the most urgent updates through the first design iteration, it was necessary to continue
          refining Bitstop’s website. The user base was now more familiar with the concept of Bitcoin ATMs, and the new
          priority was to direct users to their nearest kiosk. Also, the website was already rendering a client side,
          and it was necessary to incorporate server side rendering for better SEO.</p>
        <p>Other ongoing issues included the need to finalize Bitstop’s branding strategy and guidelines to reflect the
          new hardware and redesigned brand, and to correct any outdated information. Improvements to the user
          experience were needed as well, in order to create an efficient user dashboard for users to track their
          transaction history, manage their profile, and buy Bitcoin online.</p>
        <p>Finally, having developed a network partner program, it was now necessary to create a landing page for new
          and potential franchisees.&nbsp;</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

